      • GO

        public static final java.lang.String GO
        Fly to x y z at speed (cm/s). go x y z speed. x = -500-500 y = -500-500 z = -500-500 speed = 10-100. Note: x, y, and z values can't be set between -20-20 simultaneously. go x y z speed. Also Fly to x y z of the mission pad at speed (cm/s). go x y z speed mid. x = -500-500 y = -500-500 z = -500-500 speed = 10-100. Note: x, y, and z values can't be set between -20-20 simultaneously. mid = m1-m8.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JUMP

        public static final java.lang.String JUMP
        Fly to x y z of mission pad 1 and recognize coordinates 0 0 z of mission pad 2 then rotate to the yaw value. jump x y z speed yaw mid1 mid2. x = -500-500 y = -500-500 z = -500-500 speed = 10-100. Note: x, y, and z values can't be set between -20-20 simultaneously. mid1/2 = m1-m8.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CURVE

        public static final java.lang.String CURVE
        Fly at a curve according to the two given coordinates at speed (cm/s). curve x1 y1 z1 x2 y2 z2 speed. If the arc radius is not within a range of 0.5-10 meters, it will respond with an error. x1, x2 = -500-500 y1, y2 = -500-500 z1, z2 = -500-500 speed = 10-60. Note: x, y, and z values can't be set between -20-20 simultaneously. Also Fly at a curve according to the two given coordinates of the mission pad at speed (cm/s). curve x1 y1 z1 x2 y2 z2 speed mid. If the arc radius is not within a range of 0.5-10 meters, it will respond with an error. x1, x2 = -500-500 y1, y2 = -500-500 z1, z2 = -500-500 speed = 10-60. Note: x, y, and z values can't be set between -20-20 simultaneously. mid=m1-m8
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
